##No physical examination, no quarantine, no status of shelter volunteers

Micro Signal biz-leaders

Function introduction, define Chinese commercial power

By Ren Shangkun
Source: biz-leaders

###By Ren Shangkun
Source: biz-leaders

By Ren Shangkun

Source: biz-leaders

March 10,5:00 pm, all the shelter hospitals in Wuhan all the rest. However, there are still some outstanding issues to be addressed.

At noon on the 11th, "business people" received a call from Lan Qian, who claimed to be a security guard at the Wembley Arena Wuchang Shelter Hospital. He and his companions were asked to leave the hotel without a medical examination or quarantine.

"When I said I was recruiting volunteers, I was actually a temporary worker in a security company, " said Lan Qian, who was stranded in Wuhan after the city was sealed and later joined the shelter security patrol through an agent in a wechat group. Resting Cabin is a good thing, but he does not know where to go, can not leave Wuhan, and can not find other hotels and communities willing to shelter.

Food and shelter are a problem. More important, he says, he is a potential hazard of mobility.

Physical examination and isolation

The Temporary Security Staff recruited in the name of volunteers include migrant workers and locals living in Wuhan in addition to Lan Qian. There were about 50 people at the Shelter Hospital alone. At present, most have scattered away, leaving only a dozen or so of them "huddle together for warmth. ".

Lanqian did not understand whether there should be appropriate medical examination and quarantine measures for those who had previously worked in the shelter. According to him, some people have to go into the cabin to help doctors maintain order and evacuate patients. "Even if we don't go into the cabin, we patrol the entrance every day, and patients are also indirect contacts. ".

On March 11, the security company issued an electronic copy of the "go home" certificate, which read, "This certificate is valid for the day. ". Since noon, the security company hasn't been able to feed them for a day.

But the road home is not clear.

Dave Wong's family didn't want him to go straight home. He is also not at ease in the mind, "whether they are safe in the end, should focus on isolation or home isolation. ". He had heard that if there was a shelter in the community, the community would provide food and shelter, but his community did not. The community asked him to submit a medical report or a quarantine certificate.

"there was no medical check-up before starting the job, and the company gave some of the team members a test flight. " Another worker in the same situation spent the night in a small hotel near his home. Dave Wong stayed at the hotel, locked in a standoff with the company. Others in their wechat group responded that the community did not approve of the work certificate.

Many, including Dave Wong, were in place when the shelter hospital was first built, around February 5. When they first arrived, they were given proper face masks, protective clothing and medical gloves, which were later replaced by raincoats and rubber gloves.

"It's not a one-time thing, " said Lan, who takes the items back to his hotel every day and never disinfects them. "We're not allowed to lose them, and we have to hand them in after work. ".

Earlier, a fellow shelter security guard told "business people" that he thought it was too dangerous and left after 20 days. But because is the field stranded personnel, he did not find a suitable place to go out, a day on the street. In the end, he was placed by the government with the help of "fellow inmates" .

He never had a physical. At the time, though, the situation in Wuhan was far worse.

Accounts and good news

Money Matters, most of the time, are handled by the agencies that recruit them. At noon on the 11th, when Lan Qian was told to move out of the hotel, the company gave him only 1,000 yuan, saying the rest would be settled tomorrow. This angered him so much that he called the other workers to protest.

"The agent was asked by the Security Company to pay our bills on time, " said Lan Qian, so they were not owed wages. Blue to enter the cabin duty, the daily salary is 260 yuan / 8 man-hours, but the prerequisite requirements "to the end of the epidemic, " otherwise calculated by 230 yuan per day.

Dave Wong, who is in charge of extra patrols, earns 230 yuan a day for 12 hours and an extra 500 yuan for 30 days. However, there are other workers and Dave Wong encountered a different situation, recruitment of their agents initially oral agreement is to do a full month on 250 yuan per day, but now the money is unified into 230 yuan per day.

At Dahuashan Shelter Hospital in Jiangxia district, 30 km away, He Chong's daily salary was relatively higher. His salary is 280 yuan / 12 working hours, "outside the post 12 hours 280, inside the post 6 hours 380. ". He's been working for a month now, but he's only been paid for 15 days, and he doesn't know when the rest will be released.

"In fact, at first I thought the volunteers were free. The person who recruited me said that they could open volunteer certificates and health certificates, which would be good for later joining the Party and getting a pass to leave the Han Dynasty, " said He Chong, a migrant student stranded in Wuhan, the shelter where I came from was for room and board. He entered the job without a medical examination or any training.

After closing the cabin, the company gave him a nucleic acid test and CT, "originally also said not to arrange the quarantine, but for some reason, later allowed us to continue to live in the hotel. ".

On March 12, He Chong's security firm held a meeting. The executive gave them three options: Quarantine the hotel, go back to work, 200 a day, and negotiate with the company to return them to the community.

Later, the solution became just one: they all had to be quarantined in the hotel. But He Chong wondered if their double standard room, with its restaurant reception, was up to code.

Dave Wong and others are still making repeated calls to the 12345 for help. On the evening of the 12th, they finally got a piece of good news. The company issued a notice, "For those who have entered the cabin and worked in the contaminated area, CT and antibody tests will be carried out after the cabin is closed. If the antibody is positive, the nucleic acid test will be checked. At the same time, all personnel working in the clean area (outside) will be isolated for 14 days. For those working in the clean area, CT and antibody tests will be focused, such as antibody positive, the nucleic acid test will be checked. If the result is normal, they can rest normally or arrange themselves. ".

"In this case, there should be 12 people, and in the clean area there should be people who have already left, " said Lan, who believes he belongs in the front because he needs to be in the cabin and has had close contact with a confirmed patient. But he expressed concern about the risk to the community of those who had left without a medical examination.

Dave Wong had his doubts, too, and he felt that the notice meant that only those who tested positive would be placed in quarantine. "there were previous cases, the tests were fine, but he came home and infected his wife and children. " Because of the incubation period of the virus, so he was very worried, he claimed to be responsible for his family.

Dave Wong said he would continue to report the incident and try to get out of quarantine before going home.

Subsidies and responses

On March 10, "Life Times" received a call for help from volunteers in the Hanyang sports school's Shelter Hospital, and immediately, "after the cabin volunteers were expelled without quarantine" became a hot topic on Weibo.

On the evening of March 11, the People's Daily published a commentary saying, don't let volunteers be separated from their families... don't let enthusiasts be cold hearted, don't let the world be challenged. At 15:40 on March 12, Micro-blog@zhiyinhanyang, head of the Hanyang District Party Committee's Publicity Department in Wuhan, issued a formal response:

During the operation of the Shelter Hospital of the Wuhan Sports School, no volunteers were recruited to participate in security and cleaning services; the shelter of the Sports School purchased third-party services, entrusted Wuhan Huadun Security Service Co. , Ltd. to provide security services. Due to the tight employment of workers, Huadun Company, in the name of "paid volunteers" , recruited security personnel through Qq Group, Wechat Group, etc. , the security personnel were not volunteers and were paid according to the standard of 270-300 yuan per person per day. The sports school's shelter required Huadun to conduct isolation observation on two security personnel who entered the shelter to work and left the shelter for less than 14 days, for the other personnel involved in the security work of the shelter hospital, because they work in the open space without airtight space environment, and take effective protective measures, do not belong to the objects that need to be isolated observation; In view of the problem that some security personnel can not return to their communities for various reasons, we have urged Huadun to provide care and accommodation for them in accordance with the principle of humanization..

According to Dave Wong, the third party security companies entrusted by each district are not the same, and the volunteer team like He Chong's does not belong to the same security company, nor does Huadun.

There are 16 shelter hospitals in Wuhan. However, another recruitment message from an on-duty officer showed that volunteers like this were not only in the shelter, but also in places such as quarantine points where suspected groups of people were housed.

On March 13, the Wuhan 12345 hotline replied to "Business Figures" that it had asked Dave Wong and other security companies to arrange medical examinations and quarantine. If someone is in a similar situation, they can call the municipal hotline to respond to the problem.

"volunteers" recruited directly by the government will be quarantined for 14 days after other shelter hospitals are closed, and some may require nucleic acid and CT testing, the life times article said. Some of the agents recruited "volunteers" directly in the residence of the hotel isolation 14 days, isolation period of 300 yuan a day living allowance.

He Chong has also heard that volunteers elsewhere receive a 300 yuan per day quarantine allowance, but he isn't sure if he can get it. Blue Diving's doubt is, in the end has regarding 300 yuan's explicit stipulation. Their security company never mentioned the subsidy. In addition, the various regions during the work of the work allowance payment standard is not uniform.

Dave Wong thought about getting a physical as soon as possible and then going home after 14 days in isolation. "We are not demanding. We are only responsible for ourselves, for our families, and for society, " Dave Wong said.

Lan Qian, Dave Wong, He Chong
